The defendant Jessica L Limpert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called @ 1:49 p.m. Defendant Jessica L Limpert in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The defendant does not contest that a violation of the deferred sentencing agreement has occurred. The court enters a order vacating the deferred sentencing agreement. The court finds the defendant guilty and enters JOC. No statement by DE. Court orders: 60 days WCJ - Huber, GT, 4 days CFTS - I/S - 9 months probation. Conditions: Anger Managment and follow through, AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, N/C/C w/ Nicholas Bavinck, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP.
